data.title: Grand Duchess Xenia Alexandrovna and Grand Duke Alexander Mikhailovich
data.meta_description: Bust-length photograph of Grand Duchess Xenia Alexandrovna (1875-1960) and Grand Duke Alexander Mikhailovich (1866-1933). They are standing together, with Grand Duke Alexander to the left wearing naval uniform. The photograph is signed Xenia and Sando. Grand Duchess Xenia Alexandrovna was the eldest daughter of Alexander III, Emperor of Russia and his consort Maria Feodorovna, Empress of Russia. She married her cousin Grand Duke Alexander Mikhailovich at the Peterhof Palace in August 1894.
